        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 24 at 3:04PM EDT until June 24 at 3:45PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 303 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over West
Bloomfield, or near Southfield, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Trained spotter confirmed damaging wind in Novi.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Troy, Southfield, Royal Oak, and Birmingham around 310 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include
Franklin, Keego Harbor, Waterford, Orchard Lake, Commerce, Lathrup
Village, Bingham Farms, Farmington Hills, Pleasant Ridge, and White
Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
